verbose_text: An increased amount of O acetylated sialic acids (Neu5,9 Ac 2 -GPs ALL) on erythrocytes [XREF_BIBR] and peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMC) of patients suffering from childhood acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL) [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR] has been demonstrated using the preferential specificity of a lectin, Achatinin-H, towards Neu5,9 Ac 2 -alpha2,6-GalNAc [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
